label: Centre ID
name: centre
description: Centre identifier
coding_instructions: Enter your centre ID

label: Patient study ID
name: pid
description: Patient study identifier
coding_instructions: Enter the participant's study ID. This should be an unique number.

label: Patient name
name: name
description: Patient's name
source: 1. Participant 2. Participant relative/representative 3. Other person present who claim to know the participant 4. Hospital record
coding_instructions: Only entered on paper format

label: Patient ward number
name: ward
description: The number/name of the ward where the patient is admitted
coding_instructions: Only entered on paper format

label: Indoor file / Case record / Indoor patient department number
name: filenumber
description: The hospital specific record identification number
coding_instructions: Only entered on paper format

label: Patient's phone number(s)
name: patientphonenumber
description: Phone number(s) to the patient.
coding_instructions: Only entered on paper format. Collect as many as possible.

label: Representative's phone number(s)
name: representativephonenumber
description: Phone number(s) to patient representative(s)
coding_instructions: Only entered on paper format. Representative means for example a relative/representative or friend or someone else that the participant consent to you calling for follow up. Collect as many as possible.

label: Quality control record
name: qcrec
description: Indicates whether the record is part of a quality control session
coding_instructions: Enter whether this record is was filled out during a quality control session.
logic_prompts: "You have indicated that this is a quality control record. Are you sure?"

label: Vital signs recorded by quality control person
name: vsqs
description: Indicates wheter vital signs where recorder by quality control person
coding_instructions: Enter whether vital signs where recorded by quality control person.
logic_prompts: "Vital signs cannot be recorded by quality control person if this is not a quality control record"

label: Complete record
name: cr
description: Indicates whether the record is complete or needs to be completed later
coding_instructions: If the record is complete enter 1. If you will need to complete it later, for example to enter 30 days or six months follow up, enter 0. Once you enter 1 you will have to double enter all data and the record will be locked for further editing.

label: Informed consent
name: ic
description: Enter whether informed consent was obtained
coding_instructions: If you obtained informed consent enter 1. If you did not enter 0.

label: Age
name: age
description: The participant's age at the time of injury
source: 1. Participant 2. Participant relative/representative 3. Other person present who claim to know the participant 4. Hospital record
coding_instructions: Enter the age in whole years rounded down. If not available code as 999.

label: Sex
name: sex
description: The participant's sex
source: 1. Participant 2. Participant relative/representative 3. Other person present who claim to know the participant 4. Hospital record
coding_instructions: If not available code as 999

label: Mechanism of injury
name: moi
description: The mechanism of injury
source: 1. Participant 2. Participant relative/representative 3. Other person present who claim to know the participant 4. Hospital record
coding_instructions: Should be coded according to ICD-10, chapter XX, block V01-Y36, excluding codes listed in appendix 1 of the data dictionary. Use the online search engine http://apps.who.int/classifications/icd10/browse/2016/en#/XX. In participants for whom a traumatic mechanism is highly probable but you are unable to establish the exact mechanism at first contact, for example if the participant arrives unconscious with obvious external signs of trauma but no one is around to confirm the mechanism, enroll and attempt to confirm mechanism later.

label: Type of injury
name: tyi
description: Indicates the type of injury that the patient has sustained
source: As provided by the treating physician
coding_instructions: Ask the treating physician. If not available code as 999

label: Mode of transport
name: mot
description: The mode of transport used by the participant to reach hospital
source: 1. Participant 2. Participant relative/representative 3. Other person present who claim to know the participant 4. Hospital record
coding_instructions: If not available code as 999

label: Transfer status
name: tran
description: Indicates whether the patient was transferred from another health facility
source: 1. Participant 2. Participant relative/representative 3. Other person present who claim to know the participant 4. Hospital record
coding_instructions: If not available code as 999

label: Date of injury
name: doi
description: The date when the participant was injured
source: 1. Participant 2. Participant relative/representative 3. Other person present who claim to know the participant 4. Hospital record
coding_instructions: Code using the format YYYY-MM-DD, where YYYY is a four digit year, MM a two digit month and DD a two digit day. If not available code as 999.

label: Time of injury
name: toi
description: The time when the participant was injured
source: 1. Participant 2. Participant relative/representative 3. Other person present who claim to know the participant 4. Hospital record
coding_instructions: Code using the format HH:MM, where HH is a two digit hour and MM is a two digit minute. If not available code as 999.

label: Date of arrival to the casualty medical officer's desk
name: doar
description: The date when the participant arrived to the casualty medical officer's desk at participating centre
coding_instructions: Code using the format YYYY-MM-DD, where YYYY is a four digit year, MM a two digit month and DD a two digit day. If not available code as 999.
logic_prompts: "Date of injury cannot be after date of arrival"

label: Time of arrival to the casualty medical officer's desk
name: toar
description: The time when the participant arrived to the casualty medical officer's desk at participating centre
coding_instructions: Code using the format HH:MM, where HH is a two digit hour and MM is a two digit minute. If not available code as 999.

label: Date of arrival to admitting unit
name: doa
description: The date when the participant arrived to the admitting unit, for example ward or intensive care unit
source: 1. Project officer 2. Nurses notes in admitting unit 3. Participant 4. Participant relative/representative
coding_instructions: Code using the format YYYY-MM-DD, where YYYY is a four digit year, MM a two digit month and DD a two digit day. If not available code as 999. If the participant was not admitted enter as 0.
logic_prompts: "Date of injury cannot be after data of arrival to admitting unit", "Date of arrival to hospital cannot be after date of arrival to admitting unit"

label: Time of arrival to admitting unit
name: toa
description: The date when the participant arrived to the admitting unit, for example ward or intensive care unit
source: 1. Project officer 2. Nurses notes in admitting unit 3. Participant 4. Participant relative/representative
coding_instructions: Code using the format HH:MM, where HH is a two digit hour and MM is a two digit minute. If not available code as 999. If the participant was not admitted enter as 0.

label: Date of vital signs recording
name: dvsr
description: The date when the participant's vital signs were recorded upon arrival to participating centre
coding_instructions: Code using the format YYYY-MM-DD, where YYYY is a four digit year, MM a two digit month and DD a two digit day. If not available code as 999.
logic_checks: dvsr < doi, dvsr < doar, dvsr > doa
logic_prompts: "Date of vital signs recording cannot be before date of injury", "Date of vital signs recording is before date of arrival. Are you sure this is correct?", "Date of vital signs recording cannot be after date of arrival to admitting unit"

label: Time of vital signs recording
name: tvsr
description: The time when the participant's vital signs were recorded upon arrival to participating centre
coding_instructions: Code using the format HH:MM, where HH is a two digit hour and MM is a two digit minute. If not available code as 999.

label: Eye component of Glasgow coma scale upon arrival to emergency department
name: egcs
description: The eye component of the first Glasgow coma scale recorded when the participant arrives to emergency department at participating centre
source: Recorded by project officer using the GCS assessment aid.
coding_instructions: If not testable, for example due to severe facial swelling, use the code 99. For further details see the attached GCS assessment aid. If not available code as 999 (note that this code should only be used under exceptional circumstances and if used has to be discussed with the core team). For further details see the attached GCS assessment aid.
value_labels: "No eye opening at any time and no interfering factor", "Eye opening after finger tip stimulus", "Eye opening after spoken or shouted request", "Eye opening before stimulus", "Non testable"

label: Verbal component of Glasgow coma scale upon arrival to emergency department
name: vgcs
description: The verbal component of the first Glasgow coma scale recorded when the participant arrives to emergency department at participating centre
source: Recorded by project officer using the GCS assessment aid.
coding_instructions: If not testable, for example because the participant is intubated, use the code 99. For further details see the attached GCS assessment aid. If not available code as 999 (note that this code should only be used under exceptional circumstances and if used has to be discussed with the core team). For further details see the attached GCS assessment aid.
value_labels: "No audible response and no interfering factor", "Only moans/groans", "Intelligible single words", "Not orientated but communication coherently", "Correctly gives name, place and date", "Non testable"

label: Motor component of Glasgow coma scale upon arrival to emergency department
name: mgcs
description: The motor component of the first Glasgow coma scale recorded when the participant arrives to emergency department at participating centre
source: Recorded by project officer using the GCS assessment aid.
coding_instructions: If not testable, for example because the participant is paralysed, use the code 99. For further details see the attached GCS assessment aid. If not available code as 999 (note that this code should only be used under exceptional circumstances and if used has to be discussed with the core team). For further details see the attached GCS assessment aid.
value_labels: "No movement in arms/legs and no interfering factor", "Extends arm at elbow", "Bends arm at elbow and features clearly predominately abnormal", "Bends arm at elbow rapidly but features not predominately abnormal", "Brings hand above clavicle to stimulus on head or neck", "Obey 2-part request", "Non testable"

label: AVPU upon arrival to emergency department
name: avpu
description: Level of consciousness according to the first AVPU recorded when the participant arrives to emergency department at participating centre
coding_instructions: AVPU is a mnemonic and acronym from alert, voice, pain, unresponsive. Assign the code 3 if the participant is alert and talking to you. Assign the code 2 if the participant responds to a spoken or shouted request. Assign the code 1 if the participant responds to painful stimulus, see the GCS assessment aid for details on how to perform physical stimulation. Assign the code 0 if the participant does not respond to any stimulus and there is no interfering factor. If not testable, for example because the participant is intubated, use the code 99. If not available code as 999 (note that this code should only be used under exceptional circumstances and if used has to be discussed with the core team).

label: Systolic blood pressure upon arrival to emergency department
name: sbp
description: The first systolic blood pressure recorded when the participant arrives to emergency department of participating centre
source: 1. Recorded by project officer using an automatic blood pressure recorder in the left arm 2. Right arm 3. Monitor (only if option 1 and 2 are not possible due to interfering factors such as intravenous lines, other attached equipment)
coding_instructions: The mean of the first and second measurements will be automatically generated. These measurements should be done directly after each other. Assign the code 0 if the blood pressure is too low to be measured. If the automatic blood pressure recorder fails to record due to machine error or if the blood pressure is not available due to other reasons, use the code 999 but also alert the core team.

label: Diastolic blood pressure upon arrival to emergency department
name: dbp
description: The first diastolic blood pressure recorded when the participant arrives to emergency department of participating centre
source: 1. Recorded by project officer using an automatic blood pressure recorder in the left arm 2. Right arm 3. Monitor (only if option 1 and 2 are not possible due to interfering factors such as intravenous lines, other attached equipment)
coding_instructions: The mean of the first and second measurements will be automatically generated. These measurements should be done directly after each other. Assign the code 0 if the blood pressure is too low to be measured. If the automatic blood pressure recorder fails to record due to machine error or if the blood pressure is not available due to other reasons, use the code 999 but also alert the core team.
logic_prompts: "Diastolic blood pressure cannot be higher than systolic blood pressure", "Diastolic blood pressure cannot be higher than systolic blood pressure"

label: Heart rate upon arrival to emergency department
name: hr
description: The first heart rate recorded when the participant arrives to emergency department of participating centre
source: 1. Recorded by project officer using an automatic peripheral pulse oximeter 2. Manually recorded by counting the patients heart rate during one minute 3. Monitor (only if option 1 and 2 are not possible due to interfering factors such as intravenous lines, other attached equipment)
coding_instructions: The mean of the first and second measurements will be automatically generated. These measurements should be done directly after each other by first noting the first recording, removing the pulse oximeter and then attaching it again to record the second measurement. Assign the code 0 if the heart rate is too low to be measured. If the automatic pulse oximeter fails to record due to machine error or if the heart rate is not available due to other reasons, use the code 999 but also alert the core team.
logic_prompts: "Respiratory rate is higher than heart rate, are you sure this is correct?", "Respiratory rate is higher than heart rate, are you sure this is correct?"

label: Blood oxygen saturation upon arrival to emergency department
name: spo2
description: The first blood oxygen saturation recorded when the participant arrives to emergency department of participating centre
source: 1. Recorded by project officer using an automatic peripheral pulse oximeter 2. Monitor (only if option 1 is not possible due to interfering factors such as intravenous lines, other attached equipment)
coding_instructions: The mean of the first and second measurements will be automatically generated. These measurements should be done directly after each other by first noting the first recording, removing the pulse oximeter and then attaching it again to record the second measurement. Assign the code 0 if the blood oxygen saturation is too low to be measured. If the automatic pulse oximeter fails to record due to machine error or if the blood oxygen saturation is not available due to other reasons, use the code 999 but also alert the core team.
logic_prompts: "Blood oxygen saturation is quite high despite a low respiratory rate. Are you sure this is correct?", "Blood oxygen saturation is quite high despite a low respiratory rate. Are you sure this is correct?"

label: On oxygen support when blood oxygen saturation was recorded
name: vo2
description: Whether oxygen support was provided at the time when the blood oxygen saturation was recorded.
source: 1. Direct observation by project officer 2. Hospital record
coding_instructions: If unknown code as 999 but also alert the core team.

label: Respiratory rate upon arrival to emergency department
name: rr
description: The first respiratory rate recorded when the participant arrives to emergency department at participating centre.
source: 1. Manually recorded by counting the patients respiratory rate during one minute 2. Monitor (only if option 1 is not possible due to some interfering factor)
coding_instructions: The mean of the first and second measurements will be automatically generated. The respiratory rate should be recorded by counting for one minute. Assign the code 0 if the respiratory rate is too low to be measured. If the respiratory rate is not available due to other reasons, use the code 999 but also alert the core team.

label: Triage category
name: tc
description: Triage category as estimated by the treating physician.
coding_instructions: The triage category is assigned by the treating physician according to the categories below. Briefly inform the treating physician about the triage categories and explain that red should be assigned to the most serious patients and those patients that should be treated first. Green should be assigned to the least serious patients and those that should be treated last. Orange and yellow are intermediate categories, where orange patients are less serious than red but more serious than yellow and green whereas yellow patients are less serious than red and orange patients but more serious than green patients. The treating physician is the physician who would be triaging the patients, if there was a triage system in place. Hence, this person may vary across centres. In centres where the treatment is provided in the casualty by a CMO, then it is the CMO who should determine this variable. In centres where the CMO only decides which counter the patient should go to then it is the physician at that counter, for example surgery or orthopaedics, who assigns this variable. Code as 999 if unknown.

label: Number of serious injuries
name: nsi
description: Number of serious injuries as estimated by the treating physician. A serious injury is here defined as an injury that warrants hospitalisation.
coding_instructions: The number of serious injuries is needed for calculation of the Kampala Trauma score. The number of serious injuries is estimated by the treating physician according to the categories below. Ask the treating physician and inform her or him about the definition of a serious injury as given above. The treating physician is the physician who would be triaging the patients, if there was a triage system in place. Hence, this person may vary across centres. In centres where the treatment is provided in the casualty by a CMO, then it is the CMO who should determine this variable. In centres where the CMO only decides which counter the patient should go to then it is the physician at that counter, for example surgery or orthopaedics, who assigns this variable. Code as 999 if unknown.
value_labels: "Nil/no serious injury", "Single serious injury", "Multiple serious injuries"

label: Date of first ultrasonography
name: dus
description: The date when the participant was first examined with ultrasonography during the first 30 days of admission.
source: 1. Direct observation by project officer 2. Hospital record 3. Participant 4. Participant relative 5. Other person present who claim to know the participant
coding_instructions: Code using the format YYYY-MM-DD, where YYYY is a four digit year, MM a two digit month and DD a two digit day. Assign the code 99 if the only ultrasound performed was performed before arrival to participating centre. If the participant had ultrasound-examinations both before arrival and after arrival to participating centre enter the date when the participant had his or her first ultrasound in the participating centre. If the participant did not have a ultrasound enter the code 0. If not available code as 999.

label: Time of first ultrasonography
name: tus
description: The time when the participant was first examined with ultrasonography during the first 30 days of admission.
source: 1. Direct observation by project officer 2. Hospital record 3. Participant 4. Participant relative 5. Other person present who claim to know the participant
coding_instructions: Code using the format HH:MM, where HH is a two digit hour and MM is a two digit minute. Assign the code 99 if the only ultrasound performed was performed before arrival to participating centre. If the participant had ultrasound-examinations both before arrival and after arrival to participating centre enter the time when the participant had his or her first ultrasound in the participating centre. If the participant did not have an ultrasound enter the code 0. If not available code as 999.

label: Date of first CT
name: dct
description: The date when the participant had his or her first CT during the first 30 days of admission.
source: 1. Direct observation by project officer 2. Hospital record 3. Participant 4. Participant relative 5. Other person present who claim to know the participant
coding_instructions: Code using the format YYYY-MM-DD, where YYYY is a four digit year, MM a two digit month and DD a two digit day. Assign the code 99 if the only CT performed was performed before arrival to participating centre. If the participant had CTs both before arrival and after arrival to participating centre enter the date when the participant had his or her first CT in the participating centre. If the participant did not have a CT enter the code 0. If not available code as 999.

label: Time of first CT
name: tct
description: The time when the participant had his or her first CT during the first 30 days of admission.
source: 1. Direct observation by project officer 2. Hospital record 3. Participant 4. Participant relative 5. Other person present who claim to know the participant
coding_instructions: Code using the format HH:MM, where HH is a two digit hour and MM is a two digit minute. Assign the code 99 if the only CT performed was performed before arrival to participating centre. If the participant had CTs both before arrival and after arrival to participating centre enter the time when the participant had his or her first CT in the participating centre. If the participant did not have a CT enter the code 0. If not available code as 999.

label: Date of intubation
name: di
description: The date when the participant was first intubated during the first 30 days of admission.
source: 1. Direct observation by project officer 2. Hospital record 3. Participant 4. Participant relative 5. Other person present who claim to know the participant
coding_instructions: Code using the format YYYY-MM-DD, where YYYY is a four digit year, MM a two digit month and DD a two digit day. Assign the code 99 if the participant was intubated before arrival to participating centre. If the participant was not intubated enter the code 0. If not available code as 999.

label: Date of extubation
name: de
description: The date when the participant was extubated and not reintubated within 2 hours during the first 30 days of admission.
source: 1. Direct observation by project officer 2. Hospital record 3. Participant 4. Participant relative 5. Other person present who claim to know the participant
coding_instructions: Code using the format YYYY-MM-DD, where YYYY is a four digit year, MM a two digit month and DD a two digit day. Assign the code 99 if the participant was not extubated during the first 30 days of admission. If the participant was not intubated enter the code 0. If not available code as 999.
logic_prompts: "Date of extubation cannot be before date of intubation"

label: Date when mechanical ventilation was started
name: dmv
description: The date when the participant was first put on mechanical ventilation during the first 30 days of admission
source: 1. Direct observation by project officer 2. Hospital record 3. Participant 4. Participant relative 5. Other person present who claim to know the participant
coding_instructions: Code using the format YYYY-MM-DD, where YYYY is a four digit year, MM a two digit month and DD a two digit day. Assign the code 0 if the participant was not put on mechanical ventilation during the first 30 days of admission. If not available code as 999.

label: Date when mechanical ventilation was stopped
name: dmvs
description: The date when the participant was taken off mechanical ventilation and was not put back on mechanical ventilation within 2 hours during the first 30 days of admission
source: 1. Direct observation by project officer 2. Hospital record 3. Participant 4. Participant relative 5. Other person present who claim to know the participant
coding_instructions: Code using the format YYYY-MM-DD, where YYYY is a four digit year, MM a two digit month and DD a two digit day. Assign the code 0 if the participant was not put on mechanical ventilation during the first 30 days of admission. Assign the code 99 if the participant was put on but not taken off mechanical ventilation during the first 30 days of admission. If not available code as 999.
logic_prompts: "Date when mechanical ventilation was stopped cannot be before the date when it was started"

label: Date of admission to ICU
name: daicu

source: 1. Direct observation by project officer 2. Hospital record 3. Participant 4. Participant relative 5. Other person present who claim to know the participant

label: Time of admission to ICU

label: Date of discharge from ICU

source: 1. Direct observation by project officer 2. Hospital record 3. Participant 4. Participant relative 5. Other person present who claim to know the participant

label: Time of surgery

source: 1. Direct observation by project officer 2. Hospital record 3. Participant 4. Participant relative 5. Other person present who claim to know the participant

coding_instructions: Enter as free text extracted from the operating notes in the hospital record. Assign the code 0 if there was no surgery.

logic_prompts: "Date and time of ICU admission have to be after or the same as date and time of injury", "Date and time of ICU admission have to be after or the same as date and time of arrival", "Date and time of ICU admission have to be after or the same as date and time of vital signs recording"

label: Date and time of ICU discharge

logic_prompts: "Date and time of ICU discharge have to be after or the same as date and time of injury", "Date and time of ICU discharge have to be after or the same as date and time of arrival", "Date and time of ICU discharge have to be after or the same as date and time of vital signs recording"
